-- Cameroon’s Cocoa Farm Gate Price Dropped 0.2% in the Past Week
-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 2012-03-16T07:57:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-16/cameroon-s-cocoa-farm-gate-price-dropped-0-2-in-the-past-week.html
Cameroon’s average national farm
gate cocoa price dropped 0.2 percent to 1,067 CFA francs ($2.12)
a kilogram (2.2 pounds) in the week to March 14, according to
the Cameroon National Association of Cocoa and Coffee Producers.  The following is a table of regional farm gate rates, with
prices per kilogram in CFA francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 